From Kenneth Gilbert Subject Re quality control in medicine In article U writes Does anybody know of any information regarding the implementaion of total quality management quality control quality assurance in the delivery of health care I would appreciate any If there is enough interest I will post the This is in fact a hot topic in medicine these days and much of the medical literature is devoted to The most heavily funded studies these days are for outcome research and physicians and others are constantly questionning whether what we do it truly effective in any given QA activities are a routine part of every hospital's administrative function and are required by accreditation There are even entire publications devoted to QA Kenneth Gilbert University of Pittsburgh General Internal Medicine not a programmer